==English==
===Noun===
'''twig'''
# a small thin [[branch]] of a [[tree]] or [[bush]]

====Etymology====
* (Noun) - from the Germanic root ''twi-'', expressing (forking into) two-ness; cognate with Latin ''duo'' (two) 

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪɡ|-ɪɡ]]

