===Verb===
'''to twig'''
#([[colloquial]]) to [[realise]] something; to 'catch on'.
#:He hasn't ''''twigged'''' that we're planning a surprise party for him.

====Etymology====
* (Verb) From Irish ''tuigim'', meaning ''I understand''

